Key Summary (Form 8-K - Executive Transition):
- Executive Departure: James Sottile (EVP, Chief Legal Officer, Corporate Secretary) to retire effective December 31, 2025.
- Successor Appointment: Susan Dawson (current SVP & Deputy General Counsel) to assume the CLO and Corporate Secretary roles upon Sottile’s retirement, relocating to Las Vegas.
- Transition Terms:
- Sottile’s employment agreement extended through 2025; eligible for 2025 annual bonus if employed through year-end.
- Post-retirement consulting agreement ($11,959/month for 12 months) to aid transition.

Materiality Note: No immediate impact on capital structure or liquidity. Succession plan suggests continuity.

Summary of Material Information (ASX: SLM – Exploration Update)

  • Drilling Progress:
  • First drill hole completed at 713m depth; second hole to commence 200m west of initial site.
  • Intersected IOCG-style mineralization at 184m (visible chalcopyrite, ~0.5% Cu visual estimate).

  • Porphyry-style mineralization from 451m, with visible gold observed at 620m (~0.1 g/t Au visual estimate).

  • Assays Pending: Results expected from ALS Global in July/August 2025.

  • Next Steps:

  • 2,500m drill program planned; rig to mobilize to Ilo Este afterward.
  • Focus on validating IOCG/porphyry targets and assessing resource potential.

No capital markets or liquidity-impacting updates identified.

Summary of Material Information:

Announcement Type: Strategic Collaboration Agreement

  • Exclusive Collaboration signed with US-based Long Grove Pharmaceuticals for clinical studies and trials.
  • Key Objective: Combine Optiscan’s InVue® imaging device with Long Grove’s AK-FLOUR® contrast agent to explore new clinical applications (initially breast surgery).
  • Regulatory Impact: Data to support Optiscan’s FDA submissions for InVue®; potential expedited approvals via Long Grove’s existing drug data (CMC).
  • Term: 5-year agreement, with potential for expanded applications (gastrointestinal, robotic surgery).
  • Commercial Implication: Strengthens Optiscan’s foothold in the U.S. market and supports pipeline growth.

No capital raising, financial figures, or trading halt details disclosed.

FY25 Financial Highlights

- Revenue (inc. charge-through): $19.5bn (+7.2% YoY).

  • Hardware:

Capital & Balance Sheet

  • Capex: $552m (incl. M&A).
  • ROFE: 23% (down from 26% FY24).

FY26 Outlook

  • Early FY26 Sales Growth: +4.7% Group (ex-tobacco/Superior: +2.7%).
  • Food: +4.4% (ex-Superior).
  • Liquor: +1.5%.
  • Hardware: +1.1% (IHG +1.3%).

Strategic Updates

  • Acquisitions: Superior Foods synergies on track; Steve’s Liquor (8 stores) acquired.
  • Retail Media: LocalEyes launched; targeting $30m EBIT by FY29.
  • AI: Leveraging Microsoft partnership for debtors, HR, and compliance.

Other Material Items

  • Tobacco Illicit Market: ~40% of AU market; QLD regulatory push underway.
  • Program Horizon (ERP): On track (FY26 completion; total cost ~$290–300m).

Metcash Limited (ASX: MTS) – FY25 Results Summary

Financial Highlights

  • Revenue: Group revenue up 8.9% to $17.3bn (or 7.2% to $19.5bn including charge-through sales).
  • Underlying EBIT: Increased 2.3% to $507.8m.
  • Statutory NPAT: Up 10.1% to $283.3m.
  • Underlying NPAT: Down 2.4% to $275.5m.
  • Dividend: Final dividend 9.5 cps, total 18.0 cps (fully franked), payout ratio 72% of underlying NPAT.
  • Operating Cash Flow: Increased 11.7% to $539.0m.
  • Net Debt: $577.4m (debt leverage ratio 0.96x, target range 1.0x–1.75x).

Segment Performance

  • Food:
  • Revenue +11%, EBIT +18%.
  • Strong Supermarkets (+3.2% ex-tobacco) and Convenience growth.
  • Superior Foods acquisition contributing.
  • Tobacco sales declined -19.8% (accelerating illicit trade impact).
  • Liquor:
  • Sales +3.4%, market share gains (270bps since FY22).
  • EBIT -4.7% ($104.1m) due to lower wholesale price inflation.
  • Hardware:
  • Sales +2.4% (boosted by acquisitions).
  • EBIT -10.2% ($189.3m) due to subdued trade activity.
  • Margins: IHG 3.9%, Total Tools 11.2%.

Strategic Updates & Outlook

  • Mergers: Hardware (IHG + Total Tools) and Food (Superior + Campbells & Convenience) units consolidated.
  • FY26 Early Trading (7 weeks):
  • Group sales +4.7%, ex-Superior/tobacco +2.7%.
  • Food (+17.0% ex-tobacco), Liquor (+1.5%), Hardware (+1.1%).
  • Acquisition: Steve’s Liquor Warehouse (8 stores) announced post-period.

Key Dates

  • Dividend Record Date: 16 July 2025.
  • DRP Deadline: 17 July 2025.
  • Dividend Payment: 27 August 2025.

Material Impact: Improved cash flow, strong Food performance, and merger synergies offset by Hardware/Liquor challenges. Dividend maintained with slight payout ratio increase.

• Increased flow rates at RBD03: Average gas flow rate of 201 Mscfd over 7 days, a 35% increase vs. pre-cleanout rate (149 Mscfd).
  • Testing continuation: Additional 7-day flow test planned before shut-in for pressure analysis.
  • Total gas produced: 1,396 Mscf during initial 7-day test.
